        <div n="X12-002D" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-1"> Lean Tom: when I saw him last week on his horse a-wry&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-2"> Threaten'd loudly to turn me to stone w<hi rend="sup">th</hi>.  his sorcery;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-3"> But I think little Dan: that in spight of what our Foe says</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-4"> He'll find I read Ovid and his Metamorphosis.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-5"> For omitting the first (where I make a Comparison</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-6"> With a sort of Allusion to Putland and Harrison)</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-7"> Yet by my Description You'll find he in short is</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-8"> A Pack and a Garran, a Top and a Tortoise</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-9"> So I hope for henceforward Y<hi rend="sup">u</hi> ne'er will ask can I mawl</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-10"> This teazing, Conceited, rude, Insolent Animal</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-11"> But if this Rebuke might turn to his benefit</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-X12-002D-line-12"> (For I pitty the Man) I should be glad then of it.X12-002D   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
